      "beast_baseline": "wait what? sorry, i think i misread that. i'm not talking about metaphors or fantasy stuff, i'm looking at actual network packets and execution timestamps. can you give me a technical breakdown of the hardware or software bottlenecks that would cause jitter during high volume? specifically looking at the kernel level or NIC interrupts.",
